en_question: A city with a population of 7583 is undergoing an outbreak of a contagious disease. At the initial time t = 0 days, 3355 people have already been infected. The rate of spread of the disease is 0.89 per day. According to a model where the rate of spread is proportional to the product of the numbers of the population who have been infected and the numbers who have not, can you determine how many people will be infected after one week? Provide your answer in the nearest whole number.
